Reusable ability is also an important parameter for sensors, instant recovering feature bring sensors a great advantage especially in cases of ongoing monitoring over periods of time. We expect that the as-prepared MMM has good luminescence stability while repeatedly used, since it exhibits excellent durability in wide range pH and various kinds of ions. As shown in Fig. 7
                        , Tb-4-Msal MMM were immersed in 0.2 mM TNP solution, monitored the luminescent spectra maximum before and after immersion, then the film was washed by immersing it in the tap water for 1 min, and repeat the process above for 10 times. Through an oversimplified “ON-OFF-ON” switching process, the Tb-4-Msal MMM suffers bare of luminescence intensity loss, displays excellent reusability compared to luminescent sensors for explosives detection in other literature (Table 2
                        ). This easy recover method simplifies the practical usage in the ongoing aqueous system monitoring demand, make it a competitive candidate in various luminescent sensor.
